---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 224
  - Title: Srimad Bhagavatam
    Location: XI iii
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=The Cycle of Births and Deaths
  - 775
---
As fire assumes the forms of burning objects, so hath the
all-pervading Lord assumed the forms of beings and things.

As the flames rise and fall but not the fire itself, so birth and
death belong to the bodies but not to the Self.
